# Project Rule: YouthMentor AI

## Product

YouthMentor AI is a safe digital mentor for student wellbeing in the `growth` workspace.

- Reflective support, mood check-in, encouragement, crisis guardrails
- Growth character chat: scenario-based celebrity / religious-leader-style AI simulations + custom virtual personas
- Retention: memory, intimacy, coaching packs, reflection debrief bridge, freemium limits
- NOT therapy, diagnosis, or claims to speak officially for any real person or faith

## Routes

All features live under `/youthmentor/*` in `src/app/youthmentor/`.

Character growth features: `/youthmentor/characters`, `/characters/chat`, `/characters/insights`, `/settings`.

## Flow

Mood check-in → stress source → mentor persona → structured reflection (6 prompts) → safety pipeline → mentor response OR crisis panel → action plan → safety page → save to local history.

Optional bridge: reflection → character mentor debrief (`?debrief=1` on chat page).

Structured reflection flow remains primary; open character chat lives under `/youthmentor/characters/*`.

## Code layout

- `src/types/youthmentor.ts` — shared types
- `src/types/character-growth.ts` — memory, intimacy, coaching packs, settings
- `src/lib/youthmentor/` — risk, mentor, action-plan, storage, demo seed
- `src/lib/character-chat/` — presets, knowledge base, chat engine, growth storage, scenarios, coaching packs
- `src/lib/character-chat/knowledge/` — per-persona teachings, RAG-lite chunk retrieval
- `src/lib/ai/` — LLM provider (shared `EDULENS_*` env with EduTech)
- `src/context/CharacterChatContext.tsx` — character chat session + growth hooks
- `src/context/GrowthSettingsContext.tsx` — freemium, parent mode
- `src/context/YouthMentorContext.tsx` — session state
- `src/components/youthmentor/` — UI components
- `src/components/character-chat/` — character UI (scenarios, intimacy, coaching packs)
- `src/app/api/youthmentor/process/route.ts` — server pipeline
- `src/app/api/character-chat/route.ts` — character chat
- `src/app/api/character-memory/route.ts` — LLM memory summarization

## Safety

High-risk input must show crisis message and help links only — no normal coaching.

Never diagnose or tell users to keep secrets. Character chat must label replies as AI simulation, not the real person.

## Conventions

- UI strings and README may be English; course content may use Chinese where required
- Code comments: JSDoc
- Minimal diffs; reuse existing components
- No new resource files unless necessary (this project uses Tailwind, no image assets required)

## Commands (Windows)

Run commands separately; do not chain with `&&`.

Dev server: **port 3007** — http://localhost:3007/youthmentor (EduTech sibling uses 3006).

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
npm run build
```
